\begin{lemma}\label{lem:savior}
Let $G$ and $H$ both be $SRG(n,k,{\lambda},{\mu})$'s and let $\varphi$ be a homomorphism from $G$ to $H$. Suppose that $\varphi(u) \not\simeq \varphi(u')$. If $v$ is a common neighbor of $u$ and $u'$, then $v$ is adjacent to every vertex of $F_u \cup F_{u'}$. Moreover, if $v_1$ and $v_2$ are any two distinct vertices in $F_u \cup F_{u'}$, then $N_{v_1v_2} = N_{uu'}$.
